io.libraft.algorithm
Class RaftConstants

java.lang.Object
  io.libraft.algorithm.RaftConstants

public abstract class RaftConstants
extends Object

Default constants used in RaftAlgorithm. These constants control network timeouts, Raft algorithm timeouts, etc.

All time constants are defined in milliseconds (ms).

MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT

public static final int MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT
Minimum time interval after which a follower will:
  1. become a candidate
  2. and begin a new election cycle
if it does not hear from the current election term's leader.

Constant Field Values

ADDITIONAL_ELECTION_TIMEOUT_RANGE

public static final int ADDITIONAL_ELECTION_TIMEOUT_RANGE
Upper bound to the random amount of time added to MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT to create the actual election timeout for a candidate or follower.

To allow elections to converge quickly election timeouts are randomized. There must also be a floor to the timeouts to prevent transient conditions from triggering spurious elections. These two conditions mean that each server in the Raft cluster chooses an election timeout using the following formula: 

     ELECTION_TIMEOUT = MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT + randomIntInRange(0, ADDITIONAL_ELECTION_TIMEOUT_RANGE)
As a result, ELECTION_TIMEOUT has the following range: [MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT, MIN_ELECTION_TIMEOUT + ADDITIONAL_ELECTION_TIMEOUT_RANGE].

HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL

public static final int HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL
Time interval after which the leader generates an AppendEntries message. A new interval is started immediately after sending the messages generated in the previous one.
